26 G.S. 135-4(g), or G.S. 135-4.5, used in the calculation of the
27 retirement allowance that the member would receive under this
28 section.
29 (2)b. Determine the amount of a single life annuity that is the actuarial
30 equivalent of the amount determined under subdivision (1)
31 sub-subdivision (1)a. of this subsection, adjusted for the age of the
32 member at the time of retirement or, when appropriate, the age at the
33 time of the member's death.
34 (3)c. Multiply the annuity amount determined under subdivision (2)
35 sub-subdivision (1)b. of this subsection by the contribution-based
36 benefit cap factor.
37 (4)d. Determine the amount of the retirement allowance that results from
38 the member's membership service, service to which the member would
39 be entitled but for the adjustment under this subsection. The amount
40 shall be calculated in the same manner as the member's service
41 retirement allowance, with the following exceptions:
42 1. The applicable percentage of the member's average final
43 compensation shall be multiplied by the number of years of
44 membership service, rather than the number of years of
45 creditable service; the service.
