13 ($100,000), as hereinafter indexed, indexed under this subdivision, shall not
14 be subject to the contribution-based benefit cap. The minimum average final
15 compensation necessary for a retirement allowance to be subject to the
16 contribution-based benefit cap shall be increased on January 1 each year by
17 the percent change between the June Consumer Price Index in the year prior
18 to retirement and the June Consumer Price Index in the fiscal year most
19 recently ended, calculated to the nearest tenth of a percent (0.1%), provided
20 that this percent change is positive.
21 (4) Notwithstanding the foregoing, anything to the contrary under subdivisions
22 (1) through (3) of this subsection, the retirement allowance of a member who
23 became a member before January 1, 2015, or who has not earned at least five
24 years of membership service in the Retirement System after January 1, 2015,
25 shall not be reduced; however, the member's last employer, or if the member's
26 last employer did not report to the retirement system any compensation paid
27 to the member during the period used to compute the member's average final
28 compensation, the member's employer or employers who reported
29 compensation to the member during such period, shall be required to make an
30 additional contribution as specified in G.S. 135-8(f)(2)f., if applicable.
31 (5) For any member whose retirement allowance was (i) initially restored to the
32 pre-contribution-based benefit cap level, in accordance with G.S. 135-4(jj),
33 (ii) subsequently suspended for a period of at least three years due to the
34 member being restored to service, and (iii) recalculated based on becoming
35 reemployed for at least three years on the basis of the member's compensation
36 and service before and after the period of prior retirement without restrictions,
37 the amount required to restore the member's benefit to the
38 pre-contribution-based benefit cap level shall be reduced on a dollar-for-dollar
39 basis by the amount required to restore the initial retirement allowance."
