21 LEGISLATIVE RETIREMENT SYSTEM REEMPLOYMENT FLEXIBILITY
22 SECTION 1.4.(a) G.S. 135-3(a)(8)c. reads as rewritten:
23 "c. Unless otherwise provided, if a beneficiary who retired on an early or
24 service retirement allowance under this Article is reemployed by, or
25 otherwise engaged to perform services for, an employer participating
26 in the Retirement System on a part time, temporary, interim, or on a
27 fee for service basis, whether contractual or otherwise, and if the
28 beneficiary earns an amount during the 12 month period immediately
29 following the effective date of retirement or in any calendar year which
30 exceeds fifty percent (50%) of the reported compensation, excluding
31 terminal payments, during the 12 months of service preceding the
32 effective date of retirement, or twenty thousand dollars ($20,000),
33 whichever is greater, as hereinafter indexed, then the retirement
34 allowance shall be suspended as of the first day of the month following
35 the month in which the reemployment earnings exceed the indexed
36 amount, for the balance of the calendar year, unless the reemployment
37 earnings exceed the indexed amount in the month of December. If the
38 reemployment earnings exceed the indexed amount in December, then
39 the retirement allowance shall not be suspended. A suspended
40 retirement allowance of the beneficiary shall be reinstated as of
41 January 1 of each year following suspension. The amount that may be
42 earned before suspension shall be increased on January 1 of each year
43 by the percentage change between the December Consumer Price
44 Index in the year prior to retirement and the December Consumer Price
45 Index in the year most recently ended, calculated to the nearest tenth
46 of a percent (1/10 of 1%), provided that this percentage change is
47 positive. This sub-subdivision shall not apply to service as a member
48 of the Legislative Retirement System of North Carolina under Article
49 1A of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes."
