30 SECTION 1.5. Article 86 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
31 adding a new section to read:
32 "§ 58-86-41. Collection and reporting of contributions.
33 (a) Under rules adopted by the Board, each eligible fire department and each eligible
34 rescue or emergency medical services squad shall, on account of each eligible firefighter and
35 each eligible rescue squad worker, certify any information necessary for the proper
36 administration of the Pension Fund. The submission of this information by an eligible fire
37 department or an eligible rescue or emergency medical services squad constitutes a certification
38 of its accuracy.
39 (b) Each eligible fire department and each eligible rescue or emergency medical services
40 squad shall transmit contributions as certified under subsection (a) of this section on the forms
41 prescribed by the Board."
