41 LEIA MODIFICATIONS
42 SECTION 1.11.(a) G.S. 135-7(h) reads as rewritten:
43 "(h) Legislative Enactment Implementation Arrangement. – The Legislative Enactment
44 Implementation Arrangement, or LEIA, is established effective October 1, 2017, and placed
45 under the management of the Board of Trustees. The purpose of the LEIA is to provide for timely
46 and ongoing administrative implementation of legislative provisions regarding the retirement of,
47 or payment of retirement benefits to, public officers or public employees. The LEIA shall have
48 the following parameters:
49 (1) Administration. – The LEIA shall be administered by the Board of Trustees,
50 which shall compile and maintain all records necessary or appropriate for
51 administration. The Board of Trustees shall have full discretionary authority
Page 10 House Bill 1126-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 to interpret, construe, and implement the LEIA and to adopt such rules and
2 regulations as may be necessary or desirable to implement the provisions of
3 the LEIA.
4 (2) Funding of the LEIA. – In the event that (i) the General Assembly creates or
5 modifies any provision for the retirement of, or payment of retirement benefits
6 to, public officers or public employees that has a cost savings as measured by
7 actuarial note required by Article 15 of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes,
8 or (ii) the Board of Trustees identifies a specific administrative or information
9 technology purpose that is necessary to prevent an interruption to the normal
10 operation of the Retirement System, the Board of Trustees may direct up to
11 one hundredth percent (0.01%) of the required contributions to fund the LEIA.
12 These funds must be deposited in a separate fund from the fund into which
13 regular employer contributions are deposited for the Retirement System. The
14 Board of Trustees shall not direct any employer contributions into the LEIA
15 after January 1, 2035.
16 (3) Allocation of LEIA funds. – The Board of Trustees may allocate LEIA funds
17 to (i) the implementation of legislative provisions regarding the retirement of,
18 or payment for retirement benefits to, public officers or public employees, or
19 (ii) be used for administrative or information technology purposes, subject to
20 the following restrictions:
21 a. The Board of Trustees must identify individual implementation
22 projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds. These implementation
23 projects must be necessitated by a specific statute or session law that
24 was enacted within five years of the allocation of the funds. The Board
25 of Trustees must also identify the number of years for which each
26 individual implementation project will be paid for with LEIA funds.
27 b. For implementation projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds for
28 a period of one year or less, the Board of Trustees must determine that
29 the cost savings from implementing the project is projected to be no
30 less than half of the amount of LEIA funds utilized to pay for
31 implementation.
32 c. For implementation projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds for
33 a period of greater than one year, but not more than four years, the
34 Board of Trustees must determine that the long-term cost savings from
35 implementing the project is projected to be at least three times greater
36 than the cost of implementation.
37 d. No implementation project shall be paid for with LEIA funds for a
38 period of more than four years.
39 e. The Board of Trustees shall identify the specific administrative or
40 information technology purpose for which LEIA funds will be used.
41 Any use of LEIA funds for administrative or information technology
42 purposes requires a determination by the Board of Trustees that the
43 use of funds is necessary to prevent an interruption to the normal
44 operation of the Retirement System.purposes that the Board of
45 Trustees determines are necessary to prevent an interruption to the
46 normal operation of the Retirement System.
47 (4) Treatment of unused assets. – Any assets of the LEIA not used to pay allowed
48 administrative expenses for timely administrative implementation of
49 legislative provisions shall be transferred The Board of Trustees may transfer
50 assets of the LEIA to the Retirement System as an additional employer
51 contribution.
